The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 16: Finance minister P. Chidambaram will release a white paper on value-added tax (VAT), a new levy already cleared by most states. The switchover to the new tax regime from April was facilitated by Chidambaram?s assurance in June last year, when he promised states 100 per cent compensation for revenue losses arising during the first year. VAT panel chairman Asim Dasgupta had said earlier the paper was ready and awaiting the committee?s approval.

 New Delhi, Jan. 16: Fund managers who violate rules under the new pension system to be introduced this year will be slapped with penalties as high as Rs 25 crore. The Securities Appellate Tribunal, which resolves disputes in the capital market, will arbitrate in this segment too.

 Mumbai, Jan. 16: The Securities Appellate Tribunal has reduced a Sebi penalty on Smifs Capital Markets and its associates from Rs 3 crore to Rs 10,000. The firm had been accused of failing to adhere to disclosure norms in the acquisition of BSL shares. The tribunal called the fine ?excessive?.

 New Delhi, Jan. 16: Trai has issued fresh show-cause notices to the Tatas, Reliance and MTNL for misleading consumers by positioning their fixed-wireless phones as similar to mobiles.

 Mumbai, Jan. 16: HSBC has called its 14.6 per cent stake in UTI Bank a financial investment. ?Our stake is a good financial investment, nothing more,? HSBC India chief Niall S. K. Booker said.




